&lt;h3 id=&quot;Lasso-Regression-with-Soft-Thresholding&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Lasso-Regression-with-Soft-Thresholding&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Lasso Regression with Soft Thresholding&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Lasso Regression with Soft Thresholding&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Problem: regression with regularization&lt;br&gt;$$&lt;br&gt;&#92;min_&#92;mathbf{x} |&#92;mathbf{y}-&#92;mathbf{Wx}|_2^2+&#92;lambda|&#92;mathbf{W}|_1,&lt;br&gt;$$&lt;br&gt;where $&#92;mathbf{W}$ is weight vector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Solution: Do derivative to the cost function, and use &lt;em&gt;soft thresholding function&lt;/em&gt; $&#92;text{soft}(&#92;lambda,&#92;mathbf{W})$ as the &lt;strong&gt;subderivative&lt;/strong&gt; to replace the derivate of non-differentiable absolute function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reference: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kaggle.com/residentmario/soft-thresholding-with-lasso-regression&quot;&gt;soft thresholding with lasso regression&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
